---
import ServiceLayout from '../../components/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Parent Coaching"
  description="Parent coaching occupational therapy in Pakenham. Individual coaching sessions to provide parents with tools to support independence and family life."
  image="/images/services/parent-coaching-new.webp"
>
  <img src="/images/services/parent-coaching-new.webp" alt="Parent coaching therapy session" class="hero-image" />

  <h2>What to Expect</h2>
  <p>If your child is completing skill building OT, Equine Assisted Therapy or is disengaged with services, it is highly recommended that parents participate in coaching sessions.</p>
  <p>Parent coaching sessions will be run via telehealth or phone calls at a time that suits you, when you are away from your child.</p>
  <p>Here's what to expect when getting started with our Parent Coaching Occupational Therapy service.</p>
  <p>Please check our <a href="/faqs/">frequently asked questions</a> page for information on our fees & charges and anything you're unsure of.</p>

  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <div>
        <h3>When does Parent Coaching happen?</h3>
        <p>Your first parent coaching session will be scheduled following the initial 1-4 sessions with your child.</p>
        <p>The frequency and duration of ongoing sessions will be determined based around your individual family's needs and goals.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <div>
        <h3>What happens in Parent Coaching?</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Identify strengths and weaknesses of the child and the parent-child relationship</li>
          <li>Determine parent goals</li>
          <li>Problem solve challenges in everyday life</li>
          <li>Develop parent knowledge and skills to support their child outside of therapy sessions</li>
          <li>Provide updates on school and community-based sessions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</ServiceLayout>
